" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>我记得我被这张图说服了；并不是因为我认为假设的入侵计划看起来特别合理，而是因为它让我认真思考纳粹德国和日本帝国在占领世界其他大部分地区后是否会放过美国。他们似乎不太可能会这样做。</p><p>但当涉及到那个时代的政府沟通时，证明美国在第二次世界大战中所扮演的角色的电影只是冰山一角。罗斯福政府设立了一个完整的战争信息办公室， <a href="https://www.politico.com/story/2011/06/roosevelt-creates-office-of-war-information-june-13-1942-056772">试图让全国相信</a>美国的基本团结和自由价值观的首要地位。还有无数其他此类说服性努力，例如试图说服恐惧的美国人相信他们的非白人和共产主义盟友的著名海报。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86b968e7-f1b3-44ab-b2f4-05e3a87f2db8_560x777.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86b968e7-f1b3-44ab-b2f4-05e3a87f2db8_560x777.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86b968e7-f1b3-44ab-b2f4-05e3a87f2db8_560x777.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86b968e7-f1b3-44ab-b2f4-05e3a87f2db8_560x777.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/http